This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with improving orientation estimation for pedestrians in 3D object detection using a virtual multi-view synthesis module. It also involves the use of point clouds and RGB pixels, which are common in computer vision research. 

The Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category is also likely as the paper focuses on improving autonomous driving, which is a common application of robotics. 

The Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category is another possibility as the paper involves the use of a deep learning-based 3D object detection method and the virtual multi-view synthesis module. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also possible as the paper involves the use of advanced algorithms and techniques to improve orientation estimation for pedestrians in 3D object detection. 

Finally, the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper involves the generation of virtual viewpoints, which is a common topic in computer graphics research.
